The '''Royal Norwegian Ministry of Culture''' ({{lang-no|Kulturdepartementet}}) is responsible for [[cultural policy]], [[regulations]] and other matters related to the [[Mass media|media]] and [[sports]]. The [[ministry (government department)|ministry]] was established in [[1982 in Norway|1982]], at which time it was called the Ministry of Cultural and Scientific Affairs. Until then, the Ministry of Church and Education had had the overriding responsibility for cultural affairs in Norway. It is led by [[Trine Skei Grande]] ([[Norwegian Liberal Party|Liberal]]). The ministry reports to the [[Storting]].
