[[File:Refugeeconvention.PNG|thumb|States in the protocol concerning the status of refugees{{Legend|#00ff00|Parties to the 1951 convention}}
{{Legend|#ffff00|States in protocol 1967}}
{{Legend|#007500|States that ratified both the protocol and the convention}}
{{Legend|#b2b2b2|States that ratified neither the convention nor the protocol}}]]
The '''protocol relating to the status of refugees''' of 1967 broadens the definition of the [[Convention Relating to the Status of Refugees]] of 1951. The main point of the protocol was to "grant all refugees the same status irrespective of the effective date of the 1st of January 1951."

The protocol was completed on the 31st of January 1967 in [[New York City]]. Switzerland ratified the protocol on the 20th of May 1968.<ref>Publications from Switzerland: [https://www.admin.ch/opc/de/classified-compilation/19670017/201209280000/0.142.301.pdf ''Protokoll über die Rechtsstellung der Flüchtlinge''] (PDF) von 1968, Stand: 28. September 2012.</ref> Germany ratified it on the 5th of November, 1969,<ref>''BGBl.'' Nr. 18 vom 18. April 1970, S. 194–196: [http://www.bgbl.de/xaver/bgbl/start.xav?start=%2F%2F*&#91;%40attr_id%3D%27bgbl270s0194.pdf%27&#93;#__bgbl__%2F%2F*&#91;%40attr_id%3D%27bgbl270s0194.pdf%27&#93;__1470488491984 ''Bekanntmachung über das Inkrafttreten des Protokolls über die Rechtsstellung der Flüchtlinge.'']</ref> and Austria ratified it on the 5th of September 1973.

[[Directive (European Union)|Directive]] 2011/95<ref>EUR-Lex Doc. #32011L0095: [https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?qid=1529188882271&uri=CELEX:32011L0095 ''Directive 2011/95/EU of the European Parliament and of the Council of 13 December 2011 on standards for the qualification of third-country nationals or stateless persons as beneficiaries of international protection, for a uniform status for refugees or for persons eligible for subsidiary protection, and for the content of the protection granted'']</ref> of the [[European Parliament]], derives from this protocol, among other sources.

